From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrei Aldea <andrei@ti.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 21:20:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: ti: k3-am67a-beagley-ai: enable PCIe0 SERDES

BeagleY-AI already describes the PCIe0 root port, lane mux, reset GPIO,
PCIe power-enable pin, and SERDES1 PCIe lane. Enable the SERDES wrapper
and PHY so the PCIe root port can train a link to attached NVMe devices.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am67a-beagley-ai.dts | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am67a-beagley-ai.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am67a-beagley-ai.dts
index ee3a953d38ef..c50ca32e8f93 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am67a-beagley-ai.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am67a-beagley-ai.dts
@@ -977,7 +977,12 @@ &serdes0 {
 	};
 };
 
+&serdes_wiz1 {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
 &serdes1 {
+	status = "okay";
 	serdes1_pcie_link: phy@0 {
 		reg = <0>;
 		cdns,num-lanes = <1>;
-- 
2.39.5
